````
1. Introduction
This Privacy Policy explains how the SPECTRE Guild collects, uses, and stores personal data when you use the SC-UserTracker Discord bot. By using this bot, you agree to the processing of your data as described in this policy.

We prioritize the protection of your privacy and ensure compliance with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).

2. What Data We Collect
When you use the SC-UserTracker bot, we collect and store the following personal data:

Your Discord username: Collected when you submit a review or comment.
The reviewed user’s Discord username: Collected to associate the review with the person being reviewed.
The content of your review or comment: Stored and made publicly accessible to all bot users.
This data is securely stored in a MySQL database.

3. How We Use Your Data
The data we collect is used for the following purposes:

Displaying reviews and comments: Your reviews are shared publicly with other users.
Improving bot functionality: Your data helps us enhance the performance and features of SC-UserTracker.
We do not sell or rent your data to third parties. Data is only shared with third parties if legally required.

4. Public Visibility of Data
All reviews and comments you submit through SC-UserTracker are publicly accessible. Once submitted, there is no option to make this data private or anonymous. Other users can see your username, the reviewed user’s username, and the content of your review.

5. Data Retention
Your reviews and associated data are stored indefinitely, unless you request deletion (see Section 6). Reviews are meant to be permanent, public records available to the community.

6. Your Rights under GDPR
Under the GDPR, you have the following rights:

Right to access: You may request a copy of the data we store about you at any time.
Right to rectification: You can ask us to correct inaccurate or incomplete data.
Right to erasure: You may request the deletion of your personal data (e.g., username or reviews). Deleted reviews will no longer be visible to other users.
Right to restrict processing: You can ask us to limit the processing of your data under certain circumstances.
Right to object: You may object to the processing of your data at any time.
To exercise any of these rights, please contact us through the official SPECTRE Guild communication channels.

7. Data Security
We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your data from unauthorized access, loss, or destruction. The data collected by SC-UserTracker is securely stored in our MySQL database. While we strive to protect your data, no method of transmission or storage is completely secure.

8. Use by Third Parties
SC-UserTracker does not share your data with third parties unless required by law.

9. Changes to this Privacy Policy
We reserve the right to update or modify this Privacy Policy as needed. Any changes will be communicated through the bot or other official channels. Continuing to use the bot after such changes means you accept the updated terms.

10. Contact
For questions or concerns regarding this Privacy Policy or to exercise your rights, please contact us through the official SPECTRE Guild communication channels.
````

